      "letter": "أ",
      "name": "hamza",
      "description": "Glottal stop — like 'uh-oh'"
    },
    "tip": "ع (3ayn) is made by tightening the back of your throat — it has no English equivalent. أ (hamza) is a quick stop like the pause in 'uh-oh'.",
